The paper proposes a new approach for one-class classification using a multi-layer architecture of Kernel Ridge Regression based Auto-Encoders. This involves machine learning techniques such as unsupervised learning and semi-supervised learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with image classification (using datasets such as MNIST and CIFAR-10), which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper involves artificial intelligence techniques such as deep learning, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of regression-based classifiers could also suggest cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis and comparison with existing state-of-the-art methods, which could suggest cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a possible sub-category.
